    "longDesc": "Other specified rheumatic heart diseases",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes less common types of heart damage caused by rheumatic fever—a serious infection that can occur after untreated strep throat and permanently affect the heart's valves and muscles. Unlike the most common rheumatic heart problems (which have their own specific codes), this code is used when you have rheumatic heart disease that doesn't fit neatly into the main categories, such as unusual valve complications, specific muscle inflammation patterns, or combinations of different rheumatic heart issues. If you're seeing this code, it means your cardiologist has identified lasting damage from rheumatic fever that requires ongoing monitoring and possible medication or surgery.",
