    "plainEnglish": "Renovascular hypertension is high blood pressure caused by a blockage or narrowing of the blood vessels that supply your kidneys. When blood flow to the kidneys is reduced, your kidneys release hormones that cause your blood pressure to rise significantly. This type of hypertension is different from typical high blood pressure and may require specific imaging tests and sometimes a procedure to restore proper blood flow to the kidneys.",
