    "whoUses": "Emergency medicine physicians, cardiologists, and intensive care specialists use this code when patients arrive at the ER or hospital with severely elevated blood pressure accompanied by signs of acute organ damage. It commonly appears on EOB statements when patients have visited an emergency department or been admitted to an intensive care unit due to a sudden, severe blood pressure crisis.",
