    "plainEnglish": "Resistant hypertension means your blood pressure remains dangerously high even though you're taking three or more blood pressure medications at their maximum doses. This condition is frustrating because the usual treatment approach isn't working, and it puts you at higher risk for heart attack, stroke, and kidney damage. Your doctor will need to investigate whether something specific is causing your blood pressure to be resistant to treatment, such as sleep apnea, hormonal imbalances, or medication side effects.",
