    "longDesc": "ST elevation (STEMI) myocardial infarction involving right coronary artery",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a specific type of heart attack where a blood clot blocks the right coronary artery, one of the major vessels that supplies blood to your heart muscle. The \"ST elevation\" part refers to a distinctive pattern doctors see on an EKG (heart monitor) that indicates this is a serious, acute heart attack requiring emergency treatment. Patients typically experience severe chest pain, shortness of breath, and may have additional symptoms like pain in the right shoulder or neck, since the right coronary artery supplies the lower right portion of the heart.",
