    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a heart attack where a blood clot suddenly blocks blood flow to a specific area of the heart muscle, causing that tissue to start dying. Unlike heart attacks in the front or back of the heart, this one occurs in a less common location. You would typically experience sudden chest pain, shortness of breath, and possibly pain radiating to your arm or jaw, and this is a medical emergency requiring immediate hospital care.",
