    "shortDesc": "Oth current complications following AMI",
    "longDesc": "Other current complications following acute myocardial infarction",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes complications that develop soon after a heart attack, beyond the common ones like heart rhythm problems or heart failure. These \"other\" complications can include issues like blood clots in the heart, inflammation of the heart's protective sac, or damage to the heart's electrical system—conditions that emerge during the recovery period following the heart attack itself.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, emergency medicine physicians, and internal medicine doctors use this code when documenting complications occurring within weeks of a heart attack that don't fit into more specific categories. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients hospitalized or seen in follow-up care after experiencing an acute myocardial infarction (MI).",
