    "code": "I24.81",
    "rawCode": "I2481",
    "shortDesc": "Acute coronary microvascular dysfunction",
    "longDesc": "Acute coronary microvascular dysfunction",
    "plainEnglish": "Acute coronary microvascular dysfunction means that the tiny blood vessels in your heart are suddenly not working properly, making it difficult for blood to flow smoothly through them. This can happen even when your larger coronary arteries are normal, and it can cause chest pain, shortness of breath, or other symptoms similar to a heart attack. The condition develops quickly and may be triggered by stress, infection, or other factors that affect how these small vessels function.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists and interventional cardiologists use this code when diagnosing patients who present with acute chest pain or heart attack symptoms but have normal or near-normal results on coronary angiography. It may appear on patient EOBs related to emergency department visits, cardiac catheterization procedures, or hospitalization for acute coronary syndrome evaluation.",
