    "plainEnglish": "This code describes other types of acute heart problems caused by reduced blood flow to the heart muscle, beyond the typical heart attack patterns. These conditions develop suddenly and require prompt medical attention because the heart isn't getting enough oxygen-rich blood. You might experience chest pain, shortness of breath, or other warning signs that brought you to the hospital or emergency room.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, emergency medicine physicians, and hospitalists use this code when patients present with acute heart conditions involving insufficient blood flow that don't fit standard heart attack categories. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients hospitalized with acute cardiac events, particularly when the specific type of ischemic heart disease needs broader classification.",
