    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that you had a sudden lack of blood flow to your heart muscle, but the doctors couldn't pinpoint the exact type or location of the problem. Acute ischemic heart disease happens when a blood vessel supplying the heart becomes blocked or narrowed, preventing oxygen-rich blood from reaching the heart tissue. You may have experienced chest pain, shortness of breath, or other warning signs that prompted testing, but the diagnosis remains somewhat unclear.",
