    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, primary care physicians, and emergency medicine doctors use this code when documenting patients with heart disease caused by reduced blood flow. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements for those with a history of heart disease, as it's used for ongoing management, follow-up visits, and preventive care related to coronary artery disease.",
