    "plainEnglish": "A cement embolism occurs when bone cement (used during orthopedic surgery like joint replacement or vertebral procedures) accidentally enters a blood vessel and travels to the lungs, lodging in the pulmonary artery. This code indicates the cement has blocked blood flow in the lung arteries, but the heart has not yet developed acute failure as a result. Patients may experience chest pain, shortness of breath, or low oxygen levels depending on how much the blood vessel is blocked.",
