    "plainEnglish": "A fat embolism of the pulmonary artery occurs when fatty material (usually from bone marrow or adipose tissue) breaks loose and travels through the bloodstream, lodging in the arteries of the lungs. This code indicates the patient has this condition but is not experiencing acute cor pulmonale, which means the heart is not acutely failing from the strain. Fat emboli can occur after trauma, orthopedic surgery, or severe bone fractures, and patients may experience shortness of breath, chest pain, or rapid heartbeat.",
