    "rawCode": "I271",
    "shortDesc": "Kyphoscoliotic heart disease",
    "longDesc": "Kyphoscoliotic heart disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Kyphoscoliotic heart disease is heart damage caused by severe curvature of the spine (kyphoscoliosis). When the spine curves abnormally, it compresses the lungs and distorts the chest cavity, forcing the heart to work harder to pump blood and eventually leading to heart dysfunction and strain. Patients may experience shortness of breath, fatigue, chest discomfort, or swelling in the legs as the heart struggles to keep up with the body's demands.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists and pulmonologists use this code when treating patients with spinal deformities that have caused secondary heart problems. It commonly appears on EOBs for patients with severe scoliosis or kyphosis who develop cardiopulmonary complications, often in the context of imaging studies, cardiology consultations, or treatment for heart failure secondary to the spinal condition.",
