    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means your blood pressure in the arteries of your lungs is abnormally high, but it developed as a result of another underlying condition rather than occurring on its own. High blood pressure in the lung arteries makes it harder for your heart to pump blood through the lungs, which can cause shortness of breath, chest discomfort, and fatigue. Common causes include chronic lung disease, heart disease, blood clots, or other medical conditions that damage the lung blood vessels.",
