    "shortDesc": "Cor pulmonale (chronic)",
    "longDesc": "Cor pulmonale (chronic)",
    "plainEnglish": "Cor pulmonale is a condition where the right side of your heart becomes enlarged and weakened because it has to work too hard to pump blood through damaged or diseased lungs. This usually develops slowly over time due to long-standing lung disease (like COPD, emphysema, or chronic sleep apnea) that forces the heart to compensate, and can eventually lead to heart failure. Patients may experience shortness of breath, fatigue, swelling in the legs and ankles, and fluid buildup in the abdomen.",
