    "whoUses": "This code is primarily used by pediatric cardiologists, cardiac surgeons, and gastroenterologists who manage long-term complications in patients who have undergone Fontan surgery. It appears on EOBs when patients are being treated for swelling, drainage issues, or nutritional problems related to their post-Fontan lymphatic complications.",
