    "plainEnglish": "An arteriovenous fistula of the pulmonary vessels is an abnormal connection between an artery and vein in your lungs that allows blood to bypass the normal capillary network. This can happen from birth (congenital) or develop from injury, trauma, or previous lung surgery. The abnormal connection can cause blood to flow inefficiently through your lungs, potentially leading to shortness of breath, low oxygen levels, or heart strain as your heart works harder to compensate.",
