    "plainEnglish": "An aneurysm of the pulmonary artery is an abnormal bulging or widening of the main blood vessel that carries blood from your heart to your lungs. This weakening of the vessel wall can occur due to high blood pressure in the lungs, connective tissue disorders, or infections, and if it ruptures, it can cause life-threatening bleeding. Most people with a pulmonary artery aneurysm may not have symptoms initially, but if it becomes large or ruptures, it can cause chest pain, shortness of breath, or sudden collapse.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, pulmonologists, and interventional radiologists diagnose and manage pulmonary artery aneurysms, often using imaging like CT angiography or echocardiography. This code appears less frequently on routine patient EOBs but is common in hospital billing and specialist referral records when the condition is identified during workup for heart or lung disease.",
