    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a problem with the blood vessels in your lungs, but the specific type of disease hasn't been identified or documented. Your lungs contain a network of tiny blood vessels that carry blood through your lungs to pick up oxygen; when these vessels are diseased, they can become blocked, narrowed, or damaged, which affects how well oxygen gets into your bloodstream. Symptoms might include shortness of breath, chest pain, or fatigue, depending on how severe the vessel damage is.",
