    "plainEnglish": "This code describes fluid that has abnormally accumulated around your heart (called pericardial effusion) as a result of cancer that has spread to or directly affected the heart's protective lining. The fluid buildup can interfere with your heart's ability to pump blood effectively, potentially causing shortness of breath, chest pain, or swelling. This is a serious complication that requires prompt medical attention because the fluid may need to be drained to relieve pressure on the heart.",
