    "plainEnglish": "Cardiac tamponade is a life-threatening emergency where fluid builds up around your heart, compressing it and preventing it from pumping blood effectively. This can happen suddenly after an injury, infection, cancer, or as a complication of a medical procedure, and causes symptoms like chest pain, shortness of breath, fainting, and a weak pulse. Without immediate treatment to drain the fluid, this condition can cause shock and death.",
