    "shortDesc": "Re-entry ventricular arrhythmia",
    "longDesc": "Re-entry ventricular arrhythmia",
    "plainEnglish": "Re-entry ventricular arrhythmia is a serious heart rhythm problem where electrical signals in the heart's lower chambers (ventricles) get caught in a loop, causing them to fire repeatedly and abnormally fast. This happens when there are two electrical pathways in the heart tissue that allow the signal to circle back on itself instead of following the normal route. You might feel a racing heartbeat, chest palpitations, shortness of breath, or dizziness, and this condition requires treatment because it can reduce how effectively your heart pumps blood to your body.",
