    "shortDesc": "Myocarditis, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Myocarditis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Myocarditis is inflammation of the heart muscle itself, which can weaken the heart's ability to pump blood effectively throughout your body. This inflammation is usually caused by a viral infection (like the flu or COVID-19), but can also result from bacterial infections, autoimmune conditions, or certain medications. You might experience chest pain, shortness of breath, fatigue, or irregular heartbeats, and in severe cases, it can lead to heart failure or dangerous arrhythmias.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, emergency medicine physicians, and internal medicine doctors commonly use this code when a patient presents with heart muscle inflammation where the specific cause hasn't been identified yet. It frequently appears on EOB statements for patients who've had cardiac imaging, lab work, or hospitalization for acute chest symptoms or heart failure.",
