    "plainEnglish": "Myocardial degeneration means the heart muscle is weakening and breaking down over time, losing its ability to pump blood effectively. This can happen due to age, repeated stress on the heart, infections, toxins, or other underlying heart conditions. Patients may experience shortness of breath, fatigue, chest discomfort, or swelling in the legs and feet as the heart becomes less efficient.",
