    "plainEnglish": "Cardiomegaly means your heart is enlarged or bigger than it should be. This happens when the heart muscle becomes weakened or has to work harder than normal due to conditions like high blood pressure, valve disease, or prior heart attacks, causing it to pump less efficiently. You might not feel symptoms at first, but as it worsens, you could experience shortness of breath, fatigue, swelling in your legs, or chest discomfort.",
