    "plainEnglish": "This code describes bleeding inside the brainstem—the part of your brain that controls vital functions like breathing, heart rate, and swallowing—that occurred without a head injury or trauma. Brainstem bleeding is particularly serious because this area manages critical life-support functions, so even small amounts of blood can cause significant problems ranging from weakness or numbness on one side of the body to difficulty swallowing, vision changes, or loss of consciousness. This type of bleeding usually results from high blood pressure, abnormal blood vessels, blood clotting disorders, or certain medications that thin the blood.",
