    "plainEnglish": "A nontraumatic extradural hemorrhage is bleeding that occurs in the space between the outermost membrane covering the brain and the skull, without any head injury or trauma causing it. This bleeding happens spontaneously, often due to a ruptured blood vessel, and can put dangerous pressure on the brain. Patients may experience sudden severe headache, confusion, weakness, or loss of consciousness depending on how much bleeding occurs.",
