    "rawCode": "I6322",
    "shortDesc": "Cereb infrc due to unsp occls or stenosis of basilar artery",
    "longDesc": "Cerebral infarction due to unspecified occlusion or stenosis of basilar artery",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a stroke caused by a blockage or narrowing of the basilar artery, a major blood vessel at the base of your brain that supplies the lower part of your brain (brainstem) and back of the brain. When blood flow through this artery is blocked or severely restricted, the brain tissue it supplies doesn't get enough oxygen, leading to a stroke. Depending on the severity and location of the blockage, a person may experience weakness, difficulty with balance and coordination, vision problems, or difficulty speaking.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, stroke specialists, emergency medicine physicians, and hospitalists use this code when treating acute stroke patients. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients hospitalized with stroke, as it documents the specific cause and location of the stroke for billing and medical record purposes.",
