    "plainEnglish": "You had a stroke caused by a blood clot that formed in one of the arteries in your brain, but the exact location of the blocked artery wasn't documented or identified. When a blood clot blocks blood flow to part of your brain, that brain tissue dies because it isn't getting oxygen, which causes the stroke symptoms you experienced. This is one of the most common types of stroke and can result in temporary or permanent weakness, numbness, speech difficulties, or other neurological problems depending on which part of the brain was affected.",
