    "longDesc": "Cerebral infarction due to embolism of left cerebellar artery",
    "plainEnglish": "You experienced a stroke caused by a blood clot that traveled to an artery supplying the left side of your cerebellum, which is the part of your brain responsible for balance and coordination. When the clot blocked blood flow in this artery, brain cells in that region died because they weren't getting enough oxygen. Depending on the size and location of the stroke, you may experience dizziness, loss of balance, difficulty with coordination, weakness, or other neurological symptoms.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists and emergency medicine physicians use this code when treating acute ischemic strokes, particularly those affecting the posterior circulation of the brain. It commonly appears on hospital bills and EOB statements following emergency stroke care, imaging studies (CT/MRI), and inpatient or observation admission for stroke management.",
