    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a stroke caused by a blood clot that traveled to and blocked the arteries supplying both sides of the cerebellum, the part of your brain that controls balance and coordination. When these blood vessels become blocked, the brain tissue they supply doesn't get enough oxygen and begins to die, which can cause sudden problems with balance, dizziness, difficulty walking, and sometimes affects your ability to coordinate movements.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, emergency medicine physicians, and stroke specialists use this code when diagnosing and treating acute ischemic strokes involving the cerebellum. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients hospitalized with stroke, as it's part of documenting the specific location and cause of the brain damage for acute care billing and outcomes tracking.",
