    "longDesc": "Cerebral infarction due to embolism of other cerebral artery",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a stroke caused by a blood clot that traveled through your arteries and blocked a blood vessel in your brain. The clot originated elsewhere in your body (such as your heart or a carotid artery) and lodged in one of the smaller or less common arteries supplying blood to your brain. When that artery becomes blocked, brain tissue beyond the blockage doesn't get enough oxygen, leading to brain cell damage and the symptoms of a stroke like weakness, numbness, speech problems, or vision changes.",
