    "rawCode": "I636",
    "shortDesc": "Cerebral infrc due to cerebral venous thombos, nonpyogenic",
    "longDesc": "Cerebral infarction due to cerebral venous thrombosis, nonpyogenic",
    "plainEnglish": "A blood clot has formed in one of the veins that drains blood from your brain, causing a stroke. Unlike typical strokes caused by blockages in arteries, this one happens because a vein (not caused by infection) becomes blocked, preventing blood from draining properly and leading to brain tissue damage. You may experience sudden weakness, numbness, difficulty speaking, vision changes, or other stroke symptoms depending on which vein is affected and how much brain tissue is involved.",
