    "longDesc": "Other cerebral infarction due to occlusion or stenosis of small artery",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a stroke caused by a blockage or narrowing of a small blood vessel in the brain. Small artery disease (also called lacunar stroke) occurs when tiny arteries deep in the brain become blocked or clogged, cutting off blood flow to brain tissue. Patients typically experience sudden weakness, numbness, difficulty speaking, or vision problems on one side of their body.",
