    "longDesc": "Other cerebral infarction",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a stroke caused by a blood clot or blocked blood vessel in the brain, but the location or type doesn't fit into the more specific stroke categories. You may have experienced sudden weakness, numbness, difficulty speaking, vision problems, or loss of balance—symptoms that occur when part of your brain doesn't get enough oxygen-rich blood. This is a serious medical emergency that requires immediate treatment to prevent permanent brain damage.",
