    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a partial or complete blockage of the vertebral artery on the right side of your neck—a major blood vessel that carries blood to the back of your brain. The narrowing or blockage can be caused by plaque buildup, blood clots, or other conditions and may reduce blood flow to critical areas of your brain, potentially causing dizziness, weakness, vision problems, or in severe cases, a stroke.",
