    "plainEnglish": "Progressive vascular leukoencephalopathy is a condition where the white matter in your brain (the nerve fibers that transmit signals) gradually deteriorates due to problems with blood flow. This happens when blood vessels in the brain don't deliver enough oxygen and nutrients to the white matter over time, causing it to break down. Patients may experience progressive cognitive decline, memory problems, difficulty with coordination, weakness, or changes in mood and thinking.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists and neuroradiologists use this code when diagnosing patients with advanced brain imaging showing white matter degeneration related to vascular disease. It is more commonly seen in hospital records and specialist documentation rather than routine patient EOB statements, as it typically requires imaging confirmation and specialist evaluation.",
    "billable": true,
