    "plainEnglish": "Cerebral ischemia means that part of your brain is not getting enough blood flow and oxygen. This can happen when blood vessels in the brain become narrowed, blocked, or damaged, preventing adequate blood supply to brain tissue. Without prompt treatment, this condition can lead to stroke, brain cell damage, or permanent neurological problems.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, stroke specialists, cardiologists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing patients with inadequate blood flow to the brain. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients evaluated in emergency departments or admitted to the hospital for stroke symptoms or transient ischemic attacks (TIAs).",
