    "shortDesc": "Oth cerebrovascular disorders in diseases classd elswhr",
    "longDesc": "Other cerebrovascular disorders in diseases classified elsewhere",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a blood vessel problem in the brain that develops as a complication of another disease you already have. Rather than being a primary brain vessel condition, it means your existing illness (such as an infection, inflammatory disease, or blood disorder) has caused damage to or dysfunction of the blood vessels in your brain. Symptoms can vary widely depending on which blood vessels are affected and the underlying disease causing it.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, internists, and hospitalists use this code when documenting brain blood vessel complications secondary to conditions like infections, lupus, vasculitis, or other systemic diseases. It appears less commonly on patient EOBs than primary cerebrovascular codes because it requires documentation of both the secondary brain vessel condition and the underlying disease causing it.",
