    "longDesc": "Unspecified sequelae of nontraumatic subarachnoid hemorrhage",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes lasting problems or complications that develop after someone has had bleeding in the space around the brain (a subarachnoid hemorrhage) that wasn't caused by an injury or trauma. When the bleeding happens, it can damage brain tissue and blood vessels, leading to lingering effects like weakness, difficulty with speech, memory problems, or other neurological issues that persist long after the initial bleeding episode. The 'unspecified' part means the doctor hasn't identified exactly which specific complications the patient is experiencing.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, neurosurgeons, and internal medicine specialists use this code when treating patients recovering from a subarachnoid hemorrhage and monitoring for long-term effects. This code appears on EOBs related to follow-up care, rehabilitation, or treatment of complications resulting from the initial bleeding event.",
