    "shortDesc": "Memory deficit following ntrm subarachnoid hemorrhage",
    "longDesc": "Memory deficit following nontraumatic subarachnoid hemorrhage",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes memory problems that develop after a person has had a bleeding event in the space around the brain (subarachnoid hemorrhage) that wasn't caused by an injury or trauma. When bleeding occurs in this delicate area, it can damage brain tissue and affect how the brain processes and retains information, leading to difficulty remembering things. A patient with this condition might struggle to recall recent events, learn new information, or remember things they previously knew well.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, neurosurgeons, and hospitalists use this code when documenting cognitive complications during recovery from a subarachnoid hemorrhage, typically in hospital or rehabilitation settings. This code may appear on EOB statements when patients receive rehabilitation therapy, neurology follow-up visits, or cognitive assessments related to their brain hemorrhage recovery.",
