    "shortDesc": "Psychomotor deficit following ntrm subarachnoid hemorrhage",
    "longDesc": "Psychomotor deficit following nontraumatic subarachnoid hemorrhage",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes long-term movement and coordination problems that developed after someone had bleeding in the space around the brain (subarachnoid hemorrhage) that wasn't caused by an injury. The bleeding can damage brain areas that control muscle coordination, fine motor skills, and movement, leaving a person with lasting difficulty controlling their movements, balance, or coordination. This is a residual or permanent effect that someone continues to experience after surviving the initial bleeding event.",
