    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have trouble with your memory as a result of bleeding that occurred in your brain (not caused by an injury or trauma). When blood vessels rupture inside the brain, the bleeding can damage brain tissue and affect the areas responsible for memory, leaving you with difficulty remembering things. You may notice you forget recent events, appointments, or information more easily than before the bleeding occurred.",
