    "longDesc": "Other sequelae of other nontraumatic intracranial hemorrhage",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes long-term complications or lasting effects from bleeding in the brain that wasn't caused by an injury or trauma. These complications can include problems like weakness, speech difficulties, memory loss, or other neurological changes that persist after the initial bleeding has healed. Patients with this diagnosis have recovered from the acute bleeding event but continue to experience ongoing health effects from the damage that occurred.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists, and primary care physicians use this code when documenting follow-up care for stroke recovery and brain hemorrhage aftereffects. It commonly appears on EOB statements for ongoing rehabilitation, therapy visits, and neurological follow-up appointments in the months to years following a stroke or brain hemorrhage.",
