    "plainEnglish": "Memory deficit following cerebral infarction means you're having trouble remembering things as a result of a stroke (blood clot) in your brain. During a stroke, part of your brain doesn't get enough oxygen, and depending on which area is affected, it can damage the parts responsible for memory formation or recall. You might notice difficulty remembering recent events, names, or other information that you previously could recall easily.",
