    "longDesc": "Psychomotor deficit following cerebral infarction",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a movement or coordination problem that developed after someone had a stroke (cerebral infarction). The stroke damaged the part of the brain that controls how your body moves and coordinates actions, so you may experience clumsiness, difficulty with fine motor tasks like writing or buttoning shirts, or problems with balance and coordination. These movement difficulties are a lasting effect of the brain damage from the stroke.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, rehabilitation specialists, physical therapists, and stroke recovery teams use this code to document persistent movement or coordination problems during the recovery phase after a stroke. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements and medical records for patients undergoing stroke rehabilitation or follow-up care.",
