    "longDesc": "Frontal lobe and executive function deficit following cerebral infarction",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes problems with thinking, planning, and decision-making that developed after you had a stroke (cerebral infarction) that affected the frontal lobe of your brain. The frontal lobe controls your ability to plan, organize, focus, control impulses, and make decisions—so damage here can make these mental tasks harder than they were before. You might notice difficulty concentrating, struggling to plan or organize your day, or having trouble controlling your behavior or emotions.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists (rehabilitation doctors), and neuropsychologists commonly use this code when evaluating stroke recovery and cognitive deficits. It typically appears on EOB statements after hospitalization for stroke, during inpatient rehabilitation, or during outpatient neurology follow-up visits, and is often used to justify cognitive rehabilitation therapy.",
