    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a speech problem that developed after a stroke (brain attack caused by a blood clot). The stroke damaged the part of your brain responsible for smooth, fluent speech, so you may find it difficult to speak smoothly, experience stuttering, or have trouble getting words out naturally. This is different from aphasia (difficulty with understanding or finding words) and happens specifically because the stroke affected the motor control centers for speech.",
