    "plainEnglish": "Aphasia is a language disorder that affects your ability to speak, understand, read, or write—caused in this case by a stroke or other brain blood vessel problem (not the most common types). This occurs when damage to the language centers of your brain affects how you process and communicate words, though your intelligence and thinking remain unchanged. You might struggle to find words, have difficulty understanding what others say, or have trouble with reading and writing.",
