    "code": "I69.865",
    "rawCode": "I69865",
    "shortDesc": "Oth paralytic syndrome following oth cerebvasc disease, bi",
    "longDesc": "Other paralytic syndrome following other cerebrovascular disease, bilateral",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes weakness or paralysis affecting both sides of your body that developed after a stroke or other blood vessel problem in the brain. Unlike a typical one-sided stroke, this condition affects movement on both the left and right sides of your body, though the severity may differ between sides. This can result from damage to specific areas of the brain that control movement on both sides, and recovery depends on the location and extent of the original brain injury.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists (rehabilitation doctors), and stroke specialists use this code when documenting recovery or ongoing effects from cerebrovascular events that resulted in bilateral weakness. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving ongoing rehabilitation therapy, physical therapy, or neurology follow-up care after a stroke.",
