    "rawCode": "I69891",
    "shortDesc": "Dysphagia following other cerebrovascular disease",
    "longDesc": "Dysphagia following other cerebrovascular disease",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes difficulty swallowing that has developed as a lasting effect of a stroke or other brain blood vessel problem (other than the common types of stroke). After certain types of cerebrovascular events, the nerves and muscles that control swallowing can be weakened or damaged, making it hard to eat, drink, or manage saliva safely. Patients may experience choking, coughing when they swallow, or feel like food is getting stuck.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists (rehabilitation doctors), speech-language pathologists, and hospitalists commonly use this code when documenting swallowing problems in stroke recovery patients. It appears on EOB statements when a patient has had imaging or therapy services related to post-stroke swallowing difficulties.",
