    "rawCode": "I69892",
    "shortDesc": "Facial weakness following other cerebrovascular disease",
    "longDesc": "Facial weakness following other cerebrovascular disease",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes weakness or drooping of the face that developed after a stroke or other brain blood vessel problem. When blood flow to the brain is interrupted (from a stroke, bleed, or other cerebrovascular issue), it can damage the nerves that control facial muscles, leaving one side of the face feeling weak or drooping. You might notice difficulty smiling, closing one eye completely, or control of mouth movements on the affected side.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, stroke specialists, and primary care doctors use this code during rehabilitation and follow-up care after a cerebrovascular event. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients recovering from stroke who continue to experience facial weakness and receive therapy or monitoring for this lingering effect.",
