    "shortDesc": "Other sequelae of other cerebrovascular disease",
    "longDesc": "Other sequelae of other cerebrovascular disease",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes long-term effects or complications that result from a stroke or other brain blood vessel problem that doesn't fit into the more common categories. After a stroke, patients can experience lasting problems like weakness, difficulty speaking, memory issues, or other neurological effects weeks, months, or even years later—this code captures those ongoing aftereffects when they're caused by an unusual type of cerebrovascular event.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, rehabilitation specialists, and primary care physicians use this code when documenting follow-up care for stroke survivors dealing with residual complications. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving physical therapy, speech therapy, or ongoing treatment for stroke-related disabilities.",
