    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that you had a stroke or other brain blood vessel problem in the past, and you are now dealing with lasting effects or complications from it, but the specific type of stroke and the exact complications have not been clearly documented in your medical record. Common lingering effects after a stroke can include weakness on one side of the body, difficulty speaking, memory problems, or changes in mood. Your doctor may use this code when the medical records don't provide enough detail about which blood vessel was affected or which specific symptoms you're experiencing.",
