    "plainEnglish": "Ataxia is a loss of coordination and balance that develops after a stroke or other blood vessel problem in the brain. This can make it difficult to walk steadily, control your movements, or coordinate your arms and legs properly. The code indicates that a patient has this coordination problem as a lingering effect from a cerebrovascular event, but the specific type of stroke or brain blood vessel issue wasn't documented in the medical record.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists (rehabilitation specialists), and stroke specialists use this code when treating patients recovering from stroke with ongoing balance and coordination problems. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing physical therapy or rehabilitation following a cerebrovascular event.",
