    "plainEnglish": "This code describes long-term complications or lasting effects from a stroke or other blood vessel problem in the brain, when the exact type of initial brain injury isn't fully specified in your medical record. After a stroke or similar event, patients can experience ongoing problems like weakness, speech difficulties, memory issues, or other functional impairments that persist long after the initial incident has resolved.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, physiatrists (rehabilitation doctors), primary care physicians, and stroke specialists use this code when documenting follow-up care for stroke survivors dealing with residual effects. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving ongoing rehabilitation, therapy, or management of post-stroke complications months or years after the acute event.",
