    "shortDesc": "Atherosclerosis of aorta",
    "longDesc": "Atherosclerosis of aorta",
    "plainEnglish": "Atherosclerosis of the aorta means that fatty deposits and plaque have built up inside your body's largest blood vessel (the aorta), which carries blood from your heart to the rest of your body. Over time, this buildup narrows the vessel and reduces blood flow, potentially causing chest pain, weakness, or other complications depending on where in the aorta the narrowing occurs. This condition typically develops gradually due to high cholesterol, high blood pressure, smoking, or other risk factors.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists and vascular surgeons commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating patients with aortic atherosclerosis, often identified during imaging studies or cardiac evaluations. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients with cardiovascular disease who undergo diagnostic testing, interventional procedures, or medical management of their aortic condition.",
