    "longDesc": "Atherosclerosis of native arteries of extremities with rest pain, right leg",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have narrowing and hardening of the arteries in your right leg due to buildup of plaque (atherosclerosis), and you experience pain in that leg even when you're resting or not moving around. The restricted blood flow to your leg tissue causes this pain, which is a sign that your leg isn't getting enough oxygen-rich blood. This is a more serious stage of peripheral artery disease that requires medical attention to prevent complications.",
