    "longDesc": "Atherosclerosis of native arteries of extremities with rest pain, left leg",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a serious narrowing of the arteries in your left leg due to buildup of plaque (a condition called atherosclerosis), which has progressed to the point where you experience pain even when resting. This means the blood flow to your left leg is significantly reduced, causing discomfort that occurs without physical activity and indicates your leg isn't getting enough oxygen-rich blood. If left untreated, this condition can lead to tissue damage or loss of the limb.",
