    "longDesc": "Atherosclerosis of native arteries of right leg with ulceration of thigh",
    "plainEnglish": "You have plaque buildup (atherosclerosis) in the arteries of your right leg that has progressed to the point where it's caused an open wound or sore on your thigh. This happens when fatty deposits narrow the blood vessels in your leg, reducing blood flow, which prevents the skin from healing properly and develops into an ulcer. This is a serious condition that requires treatment to prevent infection and further tissue damage.",
