    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a serious blood vessel condition where plaque buildup (atherosclerosis) has narrowed or blocked arteries in your right leg, and this restricted blood flow has caused an open sore or ulcer to develop on your calf. The ulcer occurs because the leg tissues aren't getting enough oxygen and nutrients due to the poor circulation, making it difficult for the wound to heal properly and putting you at risk for infection.",
