    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a buildup of plaque and fatty deposits in the arteries of your left leg that are not part of a bypass graft. Over time, this buildup narrows the blood vessels, reducing blood flow to your leg tissues and potentially causing pain, weakness, or difficulty walking, especially during exercise. If severe, it can lead to tissue damage or other serious complications.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, vascular surgeons, and interventional radiologists commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating peripheral artery disease in the lower extremities. It frequently appears on patient EOB statements when imaging tests (like ultrasound or CT angiography) or procedures confirm arterial narrowing, or during follow-up visits for established vascular disease.",
