    "code": "I70.8",
    "rawCode": "I708",
    "shortDesc": "Atherosclerosis of other arteries",
    "longDesc": "Atherosclerosis of other arteries",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a buildup of plaque (made of cholesterol, fat, and other substances) in arteries throughout your body—other than the major ones like those in your heart or legs that have their own specific codes. This buildup narrows the arteries and restricts blood flow, which can lead to pain, weakness, or reduced function in whatever body part that artery supplies. You may not feel any symptoms at first, but over time this condition increases your risk of blood clots and organ damage.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, vascular surgeons, primary care physicians, and internists use this code when diagnosing arterial disease in less common locations (such as mesenteric, renal, or cerebral arteries). It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with advanced atherosclerotic disease or those undergoing imaging studies and interventions for vascular problems.",
