    "code": "I71.00",
    "rawCode": "I7100",
    "shortDesc": "Dissection of unspecified site of aorta",
    "longDesc": "Dissection of unspecified site of aorta",
    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of the aorta means the inner lining of your largest blood vessel (the aorta) has torn, allowing blood to seep between the inner and outer layers of the vessel wall. This creates a false channel within the aorta wall itself, which can be life-threatening because it may restrict blood flow to vital organs or cause the vessel to rupture. The code 'unspecified site' means your medical records don't specify exactly where along the aorta the tear occurred.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, vascular surgeons, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing aortic dissection, typically identified through imaging like CT angiography or echocardiography. This is a serious condition that commonly appears on EOB statements as it requires immediate hospitalization and often emergency surgery or intensive medical management.",
