    "rawCode": "I71010",
    "shortDesc": "Dissection of ascending aorta",
    "longDesc": "Dissection of ascending aorta",
    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of the ascending aorta is a tear in the inner lining of your aorta (the main artery carrying blood from your heart), which allows blood to seep between the layers of the artery wall. This is a serious and potentially life-threatening condition that typically causes sudden, severe chest or back pain and requires immediate emergency medical treatment. The tear can disrupt normal blood flow and potentially lead to rupture, heart attack, or stroke if not treated urgently.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, cardiac surgeons, emergency medicine physicians, and vascular surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating acute aortic dissection. This is a medical emergency diagnosis that frequently appears on EOB statements for patients receiving emergency department care, imaging studies (CT angiography), and surgical interventions.",
