    "longDesc": "Dissection of descending thoracic aorta",
    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of the descending thoracic aorta is a serious condition where the inner lining of your aorta (the largest artery in your body) tears, allowing blood to seep between the layers of the artery wall in the chest area. This creates a false channel within the aorta and can restrict blood flow to vital organs or the lower body. Patients typically experience sudden, severe chest or back pain, and this is a medical emergency requiring immediate treatment to prevent life-threatening complications like rupture or organ damage.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, cardiac surgeons, vascular surgeons, and emergency medicine physicians diagnose and treat aortic dissection in acute care and cardiac specialty settings. This code commonly appears on EOB statements when a patient has been admitted to the hospital for aortic dissection diagnosis or emergency intervention.",
