    "shortDesc": "Other arterial embolism and thrombosis of abdominal aorta",
    "longDesc": "Other arterial embolism and thrombosis of abdominal aorta",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a blood clot (thrombosis) or a traveling clot or plaque (embolism) that has blocked your abdominal aorta—the major blood vessel that carries blood from your heart to your belly, pelvis, and legs. This is a serious condition because it can restrict blood flow to vital organs and tissues in your lower body, potentially causing severe pain, organ damage, or tissue death if not treated quickly. Symptoms might include sudden severe pain in your abdomen, back, or legs, along with weakness or numbness in your lower extremities.",
