    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means a blood clot has formed in or traveled to your thoracic aorta, which is the main artery carrying blood from your heart through your chest. The clot can either form right there in the artery (thrombosis) or travel from elsewhere in your body and lodge there (embolism), and either way it can partially or completely block blood flow to vital organs and tissues supplied by that artery. This is a serious, life-threatening condition that requires emergency treatment because it can cut off blood supply to your organs.",
