    "longDesc": "Septic arterial embolism",
    "plainEnglish": "Septic arterial embolism means that a blood clot or piece of infected tissue has traveled through an artery and become lodged, blocking blood flow to an organ or limb. This condition is caused by an infection—often from bacterial endocarditis (an infection of the heart's inner lining) or another serious infection—that creates infected clots that break loose and travel through your bloodstream. Patients with this condition typically experience sudden pain, numbness, or loss of function in the affected area, and it requires emergency medical treatment because blocked blood flow can cause tissue damage or organ failure.",
