    "code": "I77.70",
    "rawCode": "I7770",
    "shortDesc": "Dissection of unspecified artery",
    "longDesc": "Dissection of unspecified artery",
    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of an artery means the inner layer of a blood vessel has torn, allowing blood to seep between the layers of the vessel wall. This can narrow or block the artery, reducing blood flow to the tissues it supplies, and in serious cases can lead to a stroke, heart attack, or organ damage depending on which artery is affected. The code indicates this condition occurred in an artery somewhere in the body, but the specific artery hasn't been identified in the medical record.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, cardiologists, neurologists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing arterial dissection, particularly after trauma, during imaging studies, or when evaluating sudden chest or head pain. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving imaging (CT, MRI, ultrasound) or interventional procedures to diagnose or treat the dissection.",
