    "code": "I77.71",
    "rawCode": "I7771",
    "shortDesc": "Dissection of carotid artery",
    "longDesc": "Dissection of carotid artery",
    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of the carotid artery means that the inner lining of one of the major blood vessels in your neck has torn, allowing blood to seep between the layers of the artery wall. This can happen from trauma (like a car accident or sports injury) or sometimes spontaneously, and it creates a partial blockage that restricts blood flow to your brain. You might experience sudden neck pain, severe headache, stroke symptoms, or vision changes, depending on how much blood flow is affected.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, vascular surgeons, and emergency medicine physicians commonly diagnose and manage carotid artery dissection using imaging studies like CT or MRI angiography. This code appears on EOB statements for patients who have experienced acute stroke or TIA symptoms and undergone emergency evaluation and treatment.",
