    "plainEnglish": "A dissection of the iliac artery means a tear has developed in the inner lining of one of the large blood vessels in your lower abdomen that carries blood to your legs and pelvis. This tear allows blood to seep between the layers of the artery wall, which can narrow the vessel and reduce blood flow, potentially causing pain, numbness, or weakness in the affected leg. This condition can happen suddenly due to trauma, high blood pressure, or certain connective tissue disorders, and requires urgent medical attention.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, interventional radiologists, and cardiologists diagnose and treat iliac artery dissection, typically in emergency or acute care settings. This code commonly appears on EOBs for patients undergoing imaging (CT/angiography), emergency room visits, or vascular interventions.",
