    "whoUses": "Neurologists, neurosurgeons, and vascular specialists commonly use this code when evaluating patients with stroke symptoms, neck pain, or imaging findings showing arterial damage. This diagnosis typically appears on EOB statements when patients have had imaging studies (like an MRI or CT angiography) or specialist consultations related to acute neurological symptoms, as vertebral artery dissection requires immediate evaluation and management.",
