    "shortDesc": "Dissection of other precerebral arteries",
    "longDesc": "Dissection of other precerebral arteries",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a tear in the inner lining of an artery in your neck or upper head that supplies blood to your brain (excluding the carotid and vertebral arteries, which have their own codes). When this tear occurs, blood can leak between the layers of the artery wall, potentially narrowing the vessel and reducing blood flow to your brain, which may cause symptoms like neck pain, headache, or stroke. This condition is called arterial dissection and can happen spontaneously or after minor trauma, and it requires prompt medical attention to prevent serious complications.",
