    "longDesc": "Thoracic aortic ectasia",
    "plainEnglish": "Thoracic aortic ectasia means that the aorta (the large artery carrying blood from your heart) has become abnormally stretched or dilated in the chest area. This condition develops gradually over time as the aortic wall weakens, causing it to expand beyond its normal size. While some people with mild ectasia may have no symptoms, others might experience chest pain, back pain, or shortness of breath, and the condition requires monitoring because a severely dilated aorta carries a risk of tearing or rupturing.",
