    "plainEnglish": "ANCA vasculitis is an autoimmune disease where your body's immune system mistakenly attacks the small blood vessels in your body, causing inflammation and damage. Your immune system produces antibodies against certain white blood cells (neutrophils), which leads to swelling and injury in blood vessels throughout your organs—most commonly affecting the kidneys, lungs, and nerves. Patients may experience symptoms like fatigue, joint pain, rashes, kidney problems, or breathing difficulties depending on which blood vessels are affected.",
