    "longDesc": "Hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia",
    "plainEnglish": "Hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia (HHT) is an inherited genetic disorder where blood vessels form abnormally throughout your body, causing them to be fragile and prone to bleeding. People with this condition typically experience frequent nosebleeds, and the abnormal blood vessels can also develop in the lungs, liver, brain, and gastrointestinal tract, potentially causing serious internal bleeding. Because it's hereditary, if you have HHT, there's a 50% chance you inherited it from a parent and a 50% chance each of your children could inherit it as well.",
