    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have inflammation and blood clots in the femoral veins (the large veins in both of your thighs) at the same time. The femoral veins are responsible for carrying blood back from your legs to your heart, and when they become inflamed and develop clots, it can cause pain, swelling, redness, and warmth in both legs. This is a serious condition that requires prompt medical treatment because blood clots can potentially break loose and travel to your lungs.",
