    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, cardiologists, pulmonologists, and emergency medicine physicians diagnose and treat this condition, often using ultrasound imaging to confirm the diagnosis. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients admitted to the hospital or seen in urgent care settings for leg pain and swelling, as bilateral phlebitis typically requires hospitalization and anticoagulation therapy.",
