    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, interventional radiologists, cardiologists, and emergency medicine physicians commonly diagnose and treat acute tibial vein thrombosis using ultrasound and other imaging. This code frequently appears on patient EOBs related to hospital admissions, emergency room visits, and vascular interventions like anticoagulation therapy or clot removal procedures.",
