    "longDesc": "Chronic embolism and thrombosis of right peroneal vein",
    "plainEnglish": "You have a blood clot that has formed in the peroneal vein (a deep vein in your right calf) and the clot is long-standing or recurring. The peroneal vein is an important blood vessel that drains blood from your lower leg, so a clot here can cause swelling, pain, and potentially prevent normal blood flow from that leg. This chronic condition means the clot didn't resolve on its own or has returned multiple times, requiring ongoing monitoring and treatment.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, interventional radiologists, and phlebologists use this code when diagnosing and treating deep vein thrombosis (DVT) in the peroneal vein. You'll likely see this code on EOB statements if you've had ultrasound imaging, specialized blood work, or vascular procedures to evaluate or treat chronic leg clotting.",
