    "plainEnglish": "This condition means you have a blood clot (thrombosis) that has formed in the peroneal vein, which is a deep vein in your lower left leg that runs alongside your shinbone. The clot has been present for a long time and may have partially or completely blocked blood flow in that vein. You might experience leg swelling, pain, heaviness, or skin discoloration in your lower leg, though some people have few or no symptoms.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, cardiologists, internists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing and managing deep vein thrombosis (DVT). It commonly appears on patient EOBs when someone has had ultrasound imaging, anticoagulation therapy, or follow-up visits for chronic leg vein problems.",
