    "plainEnglish": "You have a chronic blood clot in one of the peroneal veins in your lower leg (the veins that run along the fibula bone). This clot has been present for a long time and may cause swelling, pain, or a feeling of heaviness in your calf or foot. The condition won't go away on its own, but your doctor can manage it with blood thinners and other treatments to prevent complications like the clot breaking loose and traveling to your lungs.",
