    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a blood clot that formed in the smaller veins just under the skin on your right arm, and it happened suddenly. Superficial veins are the ones you can often see or feel near the surface of your skin, rather than the deeper veins inside your arm. You may have noticed swelling, redness, warmth, or tenderness along the affected vein.",
