    "plainEnglish": "You have a blood clot that formed suddenly in the shallow veins of your left arm, just under the skin. This can happen due to injury, prolonged immobility, or underlying blood disorders, and you may notice swelling, redness, warmth, or pain in your arm. While superficial clots are generally less dangerous than deep vein clots, they still need medical attention to prevent complications.",
