    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a blood clot (thrombosis) or blockage (embolism) in one of the large veins in your neck that carries blood back from your brain and head, and this condition has been present for a long time. Chronic means it has either been ongoing for weeks to months or has become a persistent problem rather than a sudden event. You may experience swelling in your neck or face, difficulty swallowing, or other symptoms related to impaired blood flow from your head back to your heart.",
