    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a blood clot in one of the small veins near the surface of your right leg, just under the skin. This condition, called superficial thrombophlebitis, typically causes redness, warmth, swelling, and tenderness along the vein. While usually less serious than deep vein clots, it can still cause discomfort and occasionally lead to complications if the clot travels deeper into the leg.",
