    "longDesc": "Varicose veins of left lower extremity with ulcer of calf",
    "plainEnglish": "You have enlarged, twisted veins in your left leg that have developed an open sore or ulcer on your calf. Varicose veins occur when damaged valves in leg veins allow blood to pool and stretch the vein walls, and in some cases this poor circulation can break down the skin and create a non-healing wound. This is a more serious form of varicose veins that requires medical attention to prevent infection and promote healing.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, interventional radiologists, and dermatologists use this code when treating patients with symptomatic varicose veins complicated by ulceration. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving wound care, vein treatments, or compression therapy for leg ulcers.",
