    "plainEnglish": "You have abnormally enlarged and twisted veins in your left leg, and these damaged veins have caused an open sore (ulcer) to develop on your ankle. This happens because the weakened veins don't push blood back up to your heart efficiently, causing blood to pool and putting extra pressure on the skin—eventually breaking down the tissue and creating a wound that's difficult to heal on its own.",
