    "plainEnglish": "Scrotal varices are enlarged, twisted veins in the scrotum caused by poor blood flow or weakened vein walls, similar to varicose veins you might see in the legs. This condition can cause swelling, discomfort, or a feeling of heaviness in the scrotum, and may sometimes affect fertility or sperm quality depending on severity.",
    "whoUses": "Urologists and vascular surgeons commonly diagnose and treat scrotal varices, often identified during fertility workups or physical exams for scrotal pain or swelling. This code appears on EOBs when patients undergo ultrasound imaging or surgical procedures to evaluate or repair the condition.",
