    "plainEnglish": "Pelvic varices are abnormally enlarged and twisted veins in the pelvic area (lower abdomen/pelvis region). These occur when blood pools in the veins instead of flowing smoothly back to the heart, similar to varicose veins you might see in the legs. Patients may experience pelvic pain, heaviness in the lower abdomen, or discomfort that worsens with prolonged standing or sitting.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, interventional radiologists, and gynecologists typically diagnose and treat pelvic varices, often identifying them during imaging studies for other pelvic complaints. This code appears on EOBs when imaging (ultrasound or CT) or minimally invasive procedures are performed to evaluate or treat symptomatic pelvic vein disease.",
