    "shortDesc": "Postthrombotic syndrome w/o complications of r low extrem",
    "longDesc": "Postthrombotic syndrome without complications of right lower extremity",
    "plainEnglish": "Postthrombotic syndrome is a long-term complication that can develop after you've had a blood clot (deep vein thrombosis) in your right leg. Even after the clot dissolves or is treated, the damage to the veins can cause chronic problems like swelling, pain, skin discoloration, or heaviness in that leg that may persist for months or years. In this case, the code indicates you have this condition without any serious complications like open sores or skin breakdown.",
