    "code": "I87.011",
    "rawCode": "I87011",
    "shortDesc": "Postthrombotic syndrome with ulcer of right lower extremity",
    "longDesc": "Postthrombotic syndrome with ulcer of right lower extremity",
    "plainEnglish": "Postthrombotic syndrome is a condition that develops after you've had a blood clot (typically in the leg), and it causes long-term damage to the veins that makes it difficult for blood to flow back up to your heart. In this case, you've developed an open sore or ulcer on your right lower leg as a result of this poor circulation—the skin breaks down because the damaged veins can't properly nourish and drain the leg tissue. This is a chronic condition that requires ongoing management to prevent infection and promote healing.",
