    "shortDesc": "Other specified disorders of veins",
    "longDesc": "Other specified disorders of veins",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes various vein problems that don't fit neatly into other specific categories—essentially a catch-all for less common venous (blood vessel) disorders. These conditions might involve improper blood flow in your veins, structural issues, or other venous complications that your doctor has identified but that don't match a more precise diagnosis code.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, phlebologists, cardiologists, and general practitioners use this code when documenting vein disorders that don't have their own specific code. It's moderately common on patient EOBs, typically appearing when a patient has been evaluated for vein-related symptoms or complications.",
