    "shortDesc": "Other nonspecific lymphadenitis",
    "longDesc": "Other nonspecific lymphadenitis",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes swollen lymph nodes (small immune system glands in your neck, armpits, or groin) caused by inflammation or infection, but the doctor couldn't identify a specific organism or cause. You might notice tender, enlarged lumps under your skin, sometimes with mild fever or fatigue, and your healthcare provider determined the swelling wasn't due to a particular bacteria, virus, or named condition.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care doctors, internists, and infectious disease specialists use this code when patients have lymph node swelling that doesn't fit a more specific diagnosis. It commonly appears on EOB statements when lymphadenitis is confirmed but the underlying cause remains unclear or wasn't further investigated.",
