    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, lymphedema specialists, general surgeons, and internists use this code when documenting lymphatic system disorders that aren't infectious or already classified elsewhere. It appears less frequently on EOBs than more common lymphatic diagnoses, typically when a patient has had imaging or surgical evaluation of unusual lymphatic symptoms.",
