    "plainEnglish": "Orthostatic hypotension means your blood pressure drops significantly when you stand up from sitting or lying down, which can cause dizziness, lightheadedness, blurred vision, or even fainting. This happens because your body isn't adjusting blood flow quickly enough to your brain when you change positions. Common causes include dehydration, prolonged bed rest, certain medications, or conditions affecting your nervous system's ability to regulate blood pressure.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, and neurologists commonly use this code when evaluating patients with dizziness or fainting episodes. It appears on patient EOBs when blood pressure regulation issues are documented during office visits or diagnostic testing, and it's often used to justify further workup or medication adjustments.",
