    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a dangerous drop in blood pressure that occurs during hemodialysis treatment, when a machine filters waste from your blood. When blood is removed from your body and circulated through the dialysis machine, your blood vessels can suddenly lose pressure, causing dizziness, weakness, or even fainting during or right after your treatment session. This happens because the rapid removal of fluid and changes in electrolytes can cause your blood vessels to relax too much.",
