    "plainEnglish": "Gangrene is the death and decay of body tissue, usually in the extremities like fingers, toes, or limbs, caused by loss of blood supply or severe infection. When tissue dies from lack of oxygen or blood flow, it turns dark and begins to break down, and without treatment, the dead tissue may need to be surgically removed to prevent the infection from spreading to healthy areas. This code is used when the gangrene doesn't fit into more specific categories, such as when the exact cause or location isn't classified elsewhere.",
    "whoUses": "Vascular surgeons, general surgeons, infectious disease specialists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when treating patients with tissue death from compromised circulation or infection. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients requiring hospitalization, imaging studies, or surgical intervention for gangrenous tissue removal.",
