    "shortDesc": "Postprocedural cardiac arrest following cardiac surgery",
    "longDesc": "Postprocedural cardiac arrest following cardiac surgery",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a serious complication where a patient's heart stops beating after undergoing heart surgery. The heart muscle may stop contracting effectively or completely, which is a life-threatening emergency that requires immediate resuscitation. This is distinct from a heart attack—it's specifically a complication that develops during recovery from a planned cardiac surgical procedure.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiac surgeons, cardiologists, and anesthesiologists document this code when cardiac arrest occurs as a direct complication of open-heart surgery or other cardiac procedures. This code typically appears on hospital bills and insurance statements related to inpatient surgical admissions, often reflecting the severity and emergency nature of the complication.",
