    "rawCode": "I97121",
    "shortDesc": "Postprocedural cardiac arrest following other surgery",
    "longDesc": "Postprocedural cardiac arrest following other surgery",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means your heart stopped beating during or immediately after a surgical procedure (other than heart surgery). Cardiac arrest is a life-threatening emergency where the heart suddenly loses its ability to pump blood effectively, and it occurred as a complication of your surgery rather than as a pre-existing condition. Your medical team would have taken immediate steps to restart your heart, and this code documents that this serious event happened as a result of your surgical procedure.",
    "whoUses": "Surgeons, anesthesiologists, and intensivists use this code when documenting complications in the operating room or immediate post-operative period. It commonly appears on patient EOBs and hospital bills since it affects billing complexity and length of stay, and represents a significant adverse event that must be clearly documented for medical record and quality tracking purposes.",
