    "plainEnglish": "This code describes heart failure that develops after you've had surgery (other than heart surgery). The stress and strain on your body from the surgical procedure can sometimes cause your heart to weaken or struggle to pump blood effectively in the days or weeks following surgery. This is a complication that doctors watch for closely after major operations, and patients may experience symptoms like shortness of breath, fatigue, or swelling in the legs.",
