    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you had a stroke (caused by a blood clot blocking blood flow to the brain) as a complication that developed after you had surgery—specifically a surgery that wasn't heart or blood vessel surgery. During or shortly after your operation, something caused a clot to form or travel to your brain, which prevented oxygen from reaching part of your brain tissue. You may have experienced sudden symptoms like weakness, numbness, difficulty speaking, or vision changes.",
